// The "Two Sum problem "
// Method -1 : Using the brute force method: you can do the two for loops and compare the elements and find the solution
code:

public int[] twoSum(int[] nums, int target){

    for(int i =0; i<nums.length-1;i++){
      for(int j=i+1;j<nums.length;j++){
          if(nums[i]+nums[j] == target){
                return new int[]{i,j};
          }
      }
    }
  return new int[]{};
}




//Method-2: using the HashMap : you create an empty hashmap and then in the for loop , while traversing the through the array you check for the complement of the number in the map, if i find the complement in the 
map we will return the indices and if not found in the map we append the complement and its index to the map and continuse the loo[.

public int[] twoSum(int[] nums, int target){
    Hasmap<Integer, Integer> result = new Hashmap<>();
    for(int i =0;i<nums.legth-1;i++){
      int complement = target - nums[i];
      if(result.containsKey(complement)){
          new int[]{result.get(complement),i};
      }
      map.put(nums[i],i  )
    }
}
